#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403  DURBAN - Churches and other organisations have come together and donated food parcels to those who lost everything during the floods in KwaZulu-Natal. Over 40,000 people were displaced during the floods that wreaked havoc in the province. READ: KZN floods | Hopes of finding loved ones fade Other organisations have come together to help with mop-up operations at the beach. * eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli reports.